@page "/"

<PageTitle>Odoo Mapping Tool - Home</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-4">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12 text-center mb-5">
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">Welcome to Odoo Mapping Tool</h1>
            <p class="lead">Create and manage data mappings between SQL Server and Odoo PostgreSQL databases</p>
            <hr class="my-4" />
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm hover-card">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-database-fill-gear text-primary" style="font-size: 3rem;"></i>
                    <h3 class="mt-3">Database Mapping</h3>
                    <p class="card-text">Create mappings between your SQL Server and Odoo PostgreSQL tables.</p>
                    <a href="mapping-creator" class="btn btn-primary mt-3">Get Started</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm hover-card">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-diagram-3 text-info" style="font-size: 3rem;"></i>
                    <h3 class="mt-3">Odoo Model Browser</h3>
                    <p class="card-text">Explore Odoo modules, models, fields, and relationships to create accurate mappings.</p>
                    <a href="odoo-model-browser" class="btn btn-info mt-3">Browse Models</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm hover-card">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-play-fill text-success" style="font-size: 3rem;"></i>
                    <h3 class="mt-3">Execute Mappings</h3>
                    <p class="card-text">Run your defined mappings to transfer data between systems.</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-success mt-3">Execute Mappings</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-3">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h4 class="mb-3">Understanding Odoo Relationships</h4>
                    <p>
                        Odoo uses several types of relationship fields to connect records across different tables. 
                        Understanding these relationships is critical for creating accurate mappings:
                    </p>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="card mb-3">
                                <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                                    <strong>Many2one (Many → One)</strong>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p class="small">
                                        A reference to a single record in another model. In the database, stored as a foreign key ID. 
                                        Example: <code>partner_id</code> in a sales order references a single customer.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="card mb-3">
                                <div class="card-header bg-warning text-dark">
                                    <strong>One2many (One → Many)</strong>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p class="small">
                                        The inverse of many2one, representing related records. Not stored in the database directly.
                                        Example: <code>order_ids</code> in a customer record shows all related orders.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="card mb-3">
                                <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                                    <strong>Many2many (Many ↔ Many)</strong>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p class="small">
                                        Many records related to many other records. Stored in a separate relation table.
                                        Example: <code>category_ids</code> relates products to multiple categories.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .hover-card {
        transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }
    .hover-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-5px);
    }
</style>
